	ATCMemo

			ATC_IgnoreBaseLimitations		String	'Set to YES to specify that transfer limiters related to the base case should be kept in the results. (Note: the variable name for this option is unfortunately confusing, so be careful)'
			ATC_IgnorePTDFBelow		Real	'Specify to ignore transfer limiters with an OTDF% smaller than this value.'
			ATC_IgnorePTDFBelow:1		Real	'Specify to ignore transfer limiters with an PTDF% smaller than this value.  Normally this only applies to limiters for the base case unless the Apply PTDF Cuttoff with Contingency Limiters option is chosen. '
			ATC_IncBranchCtg		String	'Set to YES to process contingencies.  If NO, then only base case transfer limiters will be examined'
			ATC_IncludePSPostCont		String	'Set to YES to enforce phase shifter control during post-contingency ATC calculations.  If YES this means that the phase shifter angle may change to keep the line flow from changing after the contingency has been applied.'
			ATC_LimitersSaved		Integer	'Specify an integer giving the maximum number of transfer limiter records to save.  Those limiters with the smallest Transfer Limitation will be saved.'
			ATC_LinCalcMethod		Integer	'Specify an integer designating the linear calculation method: 0 = Linearized AC; 1 = Lossless DC; 2 = Lossless DC with Phase Shifters'
			ATC_MaxLimCtg		Integer	'When multiple transfer limiters for the same limiting contingency are found, only this number will be kept for results.  Those with the smallest transfer limitation will be kept.'
			ATC_MaxLimElements		Integer	'When multiple transfer limiters for the same limiting element are found, only this number will be kept for results.  Those with the smallest transfer limitation will be kept.'
			ATC_MaxMWLimit		Real	'Only transfer limiters with a MW limitation smaller than this value will be kept'
			ATC_MultipleScenarios		String	'Set to YES to tell Simulator to analyze multiple ATC Scenarios'
			ATC_MultipleScenarios:1		String	'Set to YES to only monitor those branches that are defined in either the Line Rating A or Line Rating B lists.  '
			ATC_SolMethod		Integer	'Specify an integer specifying which ATC Solution Method to Use: 0 = Single Linear Step; 1 = Iterated Linear Step; 2 = Iterating Linear Step then Full Contingency Solution'
			ATC_TransferTol		Real	'When using an iterated method, specify the tolerance to use to stop iterations.'
			GenEnforceMWLimits		String	'Set to YES to specify that limiters related to the amount of reserve in the Buyer or Seller should be maintained.'
			GenEnforceMWLimits:1		String	'When set to YES, generator MW limits will be enforced for areas, zones, and superareas (either as the source or sink) if all criteria for generator MW limit enforcement are met.  For injection groups (either as the source or sink) the criteria for Allow Only AGC Units to Vary, Enforce Unit MW Limits, and Do Not Allow Negative Loads will all be checked and enforced if necessary.  When set to NO all of the options specified will be treated as FALSE.  This option applies when doing the Single Linear Step method either as a standalone method or part of one of the iterated methods.  When using the Economic Merit Order Dispatch method with injection groups, these options will always be checked and limits will be enforced if necessary regardless of this option setting.'

			IterateOnActionStatus		String	'Set to YES to model the impacts of actions with statuses other than CHECK in an iterative fashion. If set to NO, all actions will be modeled as if they are CHECK actions, which means that they are evaluated under reference case conditions.'
			OPF_SolutionType		Integer	'Set to YES to solve the Optimal Power Flow solution during each contingency.  The case must be generally configured to run an OPF solution before choosing this option.'
			ReactivePowerModel	ReactivePowerModel	String	'Specify how to model reactive power for Linearized Lossless DC calculation methods: 0 = ignore reactive power; 1 = assume constant voltage magnitude; 2 = assuming reactive power does not change'
			RetryRobustSolutionProcess	RetryRobust	String	'Set to YES to attempt a robust solution process after a solution failure'
			RTCTGAnaMode	UseIncTP	Integer	'Set to YES to use incremental topology processing for contingency analysis.  Setting to YES is recommended.'
			TSModelClass	TSModelsTrip	String	'A comma-delimited list of transient model object types which Simulator will model in the simulation of contingency analysis solutions'
			TSModelClass:1	TSModelsMonitor	String	'A comma-delimited list of transient model object types which Simulator will monitor in contingency analysis solutions with contingency violations reported as appropriate'
			TSTime	TSModelMaxDelay	Real	'When using transient stability models in contingency analysis, this is the maximum time delay for which a transient model will be treated as though it responds in the power flow contingency solution.  Thus if transient relay model has a delay of 1000 seconds, and this value is set to 500 seconds then that transient relay model will not be treated as though it responds during the power flow contingency solution'
			UseAreaPartsMakeUpPower	MakeUpPower	String	'Specify how to handle make-up power when performing contingency solutions. Choices are "Area Part Factors", "Gen Part Factors", or "Same as Power Flow".  Recommended setting is "Gen Part Factors".'

			BusName		String	'Name of the bus'
		*A*	BusName_NomVolt		String	'Name_Nominal kV of the bus'
		*1*	BusNum		Integer	'Number of the bus'
		*2B*	GenID		String	'2 character generator identification field.  Used to identify multiple generators at a single bus'
			GenMVABase		Real	'Generator's MVA base'
			Label		String	'This field is when reading from an auxiliary file (or pasting from a spreadsheet).  The label field will automatically be used as the identifying field for the object.  When shown in the user interface, the field will always shown the primary label'
			ObjectType		String	'Type of machine model'
			Selected		String	'YES or NO field which displays if record has been selected.  The field can be used in combination with numerous script commands in auxiliary files.  Is also used to help choose records in the user interface sometimes'
			SOData		String	'Name of the Default Set data that matches all the parameters for this device'
			TSDeviceStatus		String	'Status of the transient stability device'
			TSEfdMax		Real	'Maximum field voltage'
			TSEfdMin		Real	'Minimum excitation output, pu'
			TSFullSupport		String	'Fully Supported'
			TSKa		Real	'Regulator gain'
			TSKf		Real	'Regulator stabilizing circuit gain'
			TSSubIntervals		Integer	'Specify the number of sub-interval integration steps to use. A blank value will cause Simulator to use a default for that model type.  Normally a model will not use sub-interval integration. Values must be either blank, 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64 or 128'
			TSTa		Real	'Regulator amplifier time constant'
			TSTa:1		Real	'Regulator amplifier time constant'
			TSTf		Real	'Regulator stabilizing circuit time constant'

			TSGovRespLimit		String	'Determines the response of the governor control limits during a transient stability run.  Options are "Normal", "Down Only", or "Fixed".  "Normal" means that the specified governor limits are used.  "Down Only" means that the upper limit is set equal to the initial condition value (and thus control can only go down).  "Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant). "Normal" means that the specified governor limits are used.  "Down Only" means that the upper limit is set equal to the initial condition value (and thus control can only go down).  "Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant).  Note that power output can still vary for those turbines whose MW output is sensitive to speed.'

"Normal" means that the specified governor limits are used.  "Down Only" means that the upper limit is set equal to the initial condition value (and thus control can only go down).  "Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant).  Note that power output can still vary for those turbines whose MW output is sensitive to speed.'

"Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant).  Note that power output can still vary for those turbines whose MW output is sensitive to speed.'

"Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant). "Normal" means that the specified governor limits are used.  "Down Only" means that the upper limit is set equal to the initial condition value (and thus control can only go down).  "Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant).  Note that power output can still vary for those turbines whose MW output is sensitive to speed.'
			TSR		Real	'Permanent droop, pu'
			TSSubIntervals		Integer	'Specify the number of sub-interval integration steps to use. A blank value will cause Simulator to use a default for that model type.  Normally a model will not use sub-interval integration. Values must be either blank, 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64 or 128'
			TST:1		Real	'Steam bowl time constant, sec'

			TST:3		Real	'Reheater time constant, sec'

"Fixed" means that both the upper and lower limits are set equal to the initial condition (and thus control will be approximately constant).  Note that power output can still vary for those turbines whose MW output is sensitive to speed.'

MessLog_Options
			LogAutoEnableAuto		String	'Set to YES to have the log automatically written to a file'
			LogAutoFileName		String	'When autowriting the log, this is the name of the file to which the log is written'
			LogAutoWriteEveryXlines		Integer	'When autowriting the log, the log will be written to the file after this number of lines'
